# Compute the softmax probabilities
        probs = F.softmax(preds, dim=1)
        
        # Gather the probabilities of the true class
        true_probs = probs.gather(1, labels.view(-1, 1))
        
        # Compute the focal loss components
        focal_weight = (1 - true_probs) ** self.gamma
        alpha_weight = self.alpha[labels]
        
        # Compute the final focal loss
        loss = -alpha_weight * focal_weight * torch.log(true_probs)
        
        # Sum or average the loss based on size_average
        if self.size_average:
            return loss.mean()
        else:
            return loss.sum()
